## Non-Negotiables

- **Never invent colors.** Every hex value used in a concept must come from the Neon token list below.
- **Never invent font sizes or weights.** All type must use an `Inter` font and a defined token scale.
- **Never invent a widget size.** All widget dimensions must snap to the 8-column grid using one of the 7 size tiers.
- **Never use a size outside a framework's valid set.** Each framework specifies which sizes are valid — check the Framework + Size Pairing Guide before assigning a size.
- **Always justify the size choice.** Every concept must include a `Size Rationale` in its HTML comment header explaining in one sentence why the chosen size fits the content.
- **Every concept must map to exactly one framework.** If the content spans multiple frameworks, produce one widget per framework rather than mixing anatomy in a single container.
- If you need a token that is not listed below, note it as `[TOKEN MISSING — needs extraction]` and do NOT substitute an arbitrary value.

