## Widget Sizing Grid

**Source:** [UXTT-Widgets](https://www.figma.com/design/6gHlNEUBGcVMC7NJSlffXG/UXTT-Widgets?node-id=0-1) (authoritative)  
**Grid:** 8 equal columns | **Row height:** 180px | **Gutter:** 16px | **Column width at xl:** 180px

### Size Tiers

| Size | Columns | Rows | Notes |
|------|---------|------|-------|
| XXS | 2 | 1 | Minimal stat/indicator |
| XS | 4 | 1 | Compact summary |
| S | 8 | 1 | Full-width banner |
| M | 2 | 2 | Small card |
| L | 4 | 2 | Medium card |
| XL | 4 | 4 | Large data card |
| XXL | 8 | 5 (or 100%) | Full-width deep widget |

### Pixel Dimensions at breakpoints.xl (1552px content, col = 180px, gap = 16px)

Formula: Width = `(cols × 180) + ((cols−1) × 16)`. Height = `(rows × 180) + ((rows−1) × 16)`.

| Size | Width | Height |
|------|-------|--------|
| XXS | 376px | 180px |
| XS | 768px | 180px |
| S | 1552px | 180px |
| M | 376px | 376px |
| L | 768px | 376px |
| XL | 768px | 768px |
| XXL | 1552px | 964px |

**RULE:** Every widget container in a concept file must declare a `data-widget-size` attribute matching one of: `xxs`, `xs`, `s`, `m`, `l`, `xl`, `xxl`. Use the corresponding pixel dimensions from the table above.

